The problem asks for the sum of the 8 neighbors of the number $N_0 = 2026$ in a square spiral grid, starting with 1 at the center $(0, 0)$.

First, we locate $N_0 = 2026$. The numbers at the corners of the spiral squares (southeast corners) are $M_k = (2k+1)^2$.
We look for $k$ such that $M_{k-1} < 2026 \le M_k$.
$43^2 = 1849$. $k-1 = 21$, so $k=22$. $M_{21} = 1849$.
$45^2 = 2025$. $k = 22$. $M_{22} = 2025$.

The number $N=2025$ is the maximum number in Layer $k=22$, located at the Southeast corner $(k, -k)$, so $N(22, -22) = 2025$.

$N_0 = 2026$ must be the starting number of Layer $k=23$.
Layer $k$ starts by moving 1 unit East from $M_{k-1}$: $(k, -k+1)$.
$N_0 = 2026$ is located at $(x_0, y_0) = (23, -22)$.

We identify the coordinates of the 8 neighbors $C(x, y)$ surrounding $C_0(23, -22)$:
\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|}
\hline
$C_5(22, -21)$ & $C_3(23, -21)$ & $C_6(24, -21)$ \\
\hline
$C_1(22, -22)$ & $N_0(2026)$ & $C_2(24, -22)$ \\
\hline
$C_7(22, -23)$ & $C_4(23, -23)$ & $C_8(24, -23)$ \\
\hline
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

We calculate the value $N(x, y)$ for each neighbor based on its layer $k' = \max(|x|, |y|)$:

1. **$k'=22$ neighbors** (West):
$C_1(22, -22)$: This is the SE corner of Layer 22.
$N_1 = M_{22} = 2025$.
$C_5(22, -21)$: This is the starting point of Layer 22, $N_{start}(22) = M_{21} + 1 = 1849 + 1$.
$N_5 = 1850$.

2. **$k'=23$ neighbors** (Same layer as $N_0$):
$N_{start}(23) = 2026$ at $(23, -22)$. The path increases $y$ (North) along $x=23$.
$C_3(23, -21)$: 1 step North from $N_0$.
$N_3 = 2026 + 1 = 2027$.
$C_4(23, -23)$: This is the SE corner of Layer 23, $M_{23} = 47^2$.
$N_4 = 2209$.
$C_7(22, -23)$: This point lies on the South side of Layer 23, $y=-23$. The South side path runs Eastward towards $N_4$. $C_7$ is 1 step West of $N_4$.
$N_7 = 2209 - 1 = 2208$.

3. **$k'=24$ neighbors** (East):
$M_{23} = 2209$. $N_{start}(24) = 2210$. Layer 24 starts at $(24, -23)$.
$C_8(24, -23)$: This is $N_{start}(24)$.
$N_8 = 2210$.
The path proceeds North along $x=24$.
$C_2(24, -22)$: 1 step North from $N_8$.
$N_2 = 2210 + 1 = 2211$.
$C_6(24, -21)$: 2 steps North from $N_8$.
$N_6 = 2210 + 2 = 2212$.

The 8 neighbor values are:
$N_1 = 2025$
$N_2 = 2211$
$N_3 = 2027$
$N_4 = 2209$
$N_5 = 1850$
$N_6 = 2212$
$N_7 = 2208$
$N_8 = 2210$

Summing the values:
$$S = 2025 + 2211 + 2027 + 2209 + 1850 + 2212 + 2208 + 2210$$
$$S = (2025 + 2027) + 1850 + (2209 + 2208) + (2210 + 2211 + 2212)$$
$$S = 4052 + 1850 + 4417 + 6633$$
$$S = 5902 + 4417 + 6633 = 10319 + 6633 = 16952$$
